    {
      "id": "3e97e125-ec4c-4c0f-8ca6-d4c4b9fbe7b3",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Moreover, the authors make a comparison between training paradigms. On the first, each dataset is trained independently and performance is assessed on the data the models were trained on. On the second paradigm, the authors pre-train a model in one dataset to then fine-tune with the other. Resutlts show that multi-task models were able to improve performance for one the tasks, but not for both. Moreover, transfer learning also seems to contribute to improvements in model performance. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "3e97e125-ec4c-4c0f-8ca6-d4c4b9fbe7b3",
        "parent": {
